$interpreted: Douglas: Commander of the Royal Infantry, Protector of the King, Hero of the Border Wars...
Douglas: Why would the grand Dylan Levon visit a forgotten old noble like myself in the middle of the night?
Dylan: There is one thing I would like to ask Sir Vincent.
Dylan: His Majesty Theodore was attacked on his hunting trip. Have you heard about the incident?
Douglas: Of course.
Dylan: For the past two weeks, the Royal Infantry has been hunting down gangs in the capital.
Dylan: We are both making the capital safer and hunting down the potential culprit.
Douglas: I'm sure the regent will take note of the Royal Infantry's hard work.
Dylan: During the investigation, I found something that caught me by surprise. The Buck is the icon of the Vincent family, am I right?
Douglas: The Buck symbolizes a strong body and a wise mind.
Douglas: Every member of the Vincent family serves the decendents of the dragonslayer with these ideals in mind.
Dylan: If so, can you show me the Vincent family's token of loyalty?
Dylan: Is this the item you are looking for?
Douglas: If that were a magic trick, you'd be gettting a huge round of applause right about now...
Dylan: Let's cut to the chase, there's something I need to as you about.
Dylan: "The wings of the Half-Blood...
Douglas: ...shall swipe away the imposter, who blocks the sun."
Dylan: !?
Douglas: I see. I was not expecting you to be one of us...
Dylan: Douglas Vincent, as commander of the Royal Infantry, I hereby arrest you for attempting to assassinate His Majesty Theodore.
Dylan: Please come with me to explain the details of this very incident!
Douglas: Damn... You have no right to accuse me with such little evidence. You will pay for such insolence. Anyone here!? Help!
Cecil: Father!?
Cecil: Curses, you filthy peasant. What are you doing to my father?
Cecil: Let go of my father, you bastard! Do you realize that your actions go against the Twelve Nobles!?
Dylan: I will make sure Douglas Vincent has a proper and fair trial.
Dylan: If Sir Vincent is indeed innocent, I will offer my humble apology and take the punishment I deserve from His Majesty Theodore and the Twelve Nobles!
